  <prompt>
    Smoke-test the complete `insights.query` tool integration end-to-end against the
    Spaarke Dev BFF deployment, using the Wave D7 synthetic test entities reserved by
    the Insights Engine r2 team for cross-project consumer validation:

    - Matter:  `da116923-d65a-f111-a825-3833c5d9bcb1`
    - Project: `27845394-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`
    - Invoice: `05c8ef8d-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`

    This task is the binding evidence layer for spec.md SC-11 + SC-18 â€” the two
    success criteria that gate Phase 2 ship. It exercises (a) the in-process
    Assistant tool catalog registration from task 024, (b) the HTTP transport from
    task 025 (subject resolution + `@spaarke/auth` `authenticatedFetch` +
    `x-correlation-id` propagation), (c) the two-path `InsightsResponseRenderer`
    from task 026 (playbook structured envelope + RAG citation-grounded prose +
    decline + empty-results sub-renderers), (d) v1.1 clickable citations / v1.0
    fallback from task 027, (e) the confidence floor badge from task 028, and (f)
    the full 12-code error matrix + retry policy + correlation-id surfacing from
    task 029.

    The task ships THREE concrete artifacts:

    1. **15-question Spaarke Dev smoke matrix** â€” 5 realistic questions per
       practice area (CTRNS contracts/transactional, IPPAT IP/patents, BNKF
       banking/finance) per integration brief Â§8. The matrix is executed against
       Spaarke Dev BFF (`https://spaarke-bff-dev.azurewebsites.net/api/insights/assistant/query`)
       via the existing R5 chat-agent path (NOT via direct `curl` â€” the chat-agent
       path is what's being validated). Each question's response is graded against
       the binding contract â€” playbook envelope present and well-formed OR RAG
       citations grounded + non-fabricated. Pass criteria are recorded in task
       notes; raw response content is NEVER committed (per integration brief Â§5.2
       no-information-leakage discipline + R5 CLAUDE.md Â§3.5).

    2. **SME walkthrough coordination + signoff** â€” 1 legal-ops SME minimum walks
       through the 15-question matrix on Spaarke Dev tenant. Operator coordinates
       SME participation (this task is OPERATOR-LED for the SME-availability
       portion; the AI agent prepares the walkthrough script + grading rubric +
       evidence-capture template and supports the operator). SME signoff is
       recorded by name + date in task notes; raw SME observations are
       paraphrased / summarized for the notes (NEVER verbatim if they contain
       customer-data references â€” Spaarke Dev synthetic entities are designed for
       this exact reason, but the discipline is reinforced here).

    3. **Findings capture + remediation backlog** â€” Any defects, UX rough edges,
       cross-tool disambiguation surprises (e.g., `/summarize` vs `insights.query`
       routing), v1.0 â†” v1.1 contract behavior drift (especially around `citations[].href`
       per FR-11 Wave F spike outcome), or low-confidence-badge calibration
       observations are filed as ranked findings. Severity-1 findings block task
       031 (Phase 2 verification); Severity-2/3 findings feed the R6 backlog per
       D3-05.

    This task is **PURE TEST + DOCUMENTATION** â€” ZERO production code change.
    BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no `dotnet publish` measurement required;
    confirm = 0 MB in task notes per R5 CLAUDE.md Â§3.6).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior QA / integration test engineer with deep familiarity of the Spaarke
    AI integration test harness (`tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/`), the
    existing `IntegrationTestFixture` pattern, the R5 chat-agent tool surface
    (tasks 024â€“029), and the Insights v1.0 binding contract (integration brief).
    Comfortable coordinating SME participation, designing pass/fail rubrics for
    LLM-generated responses, and applying ADR-018 information-leakage discipline
    when capturing evidence. Familiar with ADR-013 Â§3.5 Zone B consumer boundary
    (R5 consumes the HTTP contract ONLY â€” smoke tests assert wire-level behavior,
    NOT Insights internals).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete deliverables, all on the R5 branch (no production code change):

    1. **`tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/InsightsToolIntegrationTests.cs`**
       (NEW) â€” xUnit integration test class following the existing
       `IntegrationTestFixture` pattern. Tests are tagged with the existing
       Spaarke `[Trait("Category", "Integration")]` + new
       `[Trait("Feature", "InsightsTool")]`. Each test corresponds to one of the
       15 smoke questions; tests authenticate via the existing fixture's OBO
       flow, issue the request through the R5 chat-agent tool surface (task 024
       `InsightsQueryToolHandler` â€” NOT raw HTTP), assert the response shape
       matches the binding contract (`path` is `"playbook"` or `"rag"`;
       `citations[]` shape valid; `confidence` in [0,1]; `correlationId` echoed;
       no fabricated content per FR-04 anti-hallucination). Tests SKIP gracefully
       when Spaarke Dev is unreachable (per existing fixture pattern; see
       `PlaybookExecutionIntegrationTests.cs`). Raw response bodies are NOT
       asserted character-by-character; tests assert structural conformance to
       contract + categorical correctness rubric (defined in &lt;steps&gt; Step 5).

    2. **`projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/task-030-smoke-evidence.md`**
       (NEW, ephemeral notes) â€” Smoke test execution log. Records: 15 questions
       executed + structural-pass / structural-fail per question + categorical
       assessment (response usable / not-usable / inconclusive) WITHOUT raw
       content (per integration brief Â§5.2 information-leakage discipline). Per
       practice area: aggregate verdict + notable patterns. End-to-end
       `correlationId` traced through one representative request (smoke test
       captures the ID returned in the HTTP response header chain; if Spaarke
       Dev App Insights / Kusto is operator-accessible, the operator captures
       the trace and pastes the query result reference â€” NOT the trace body â€”
       into the notes). BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB confirmation. Zero-new-
       dependencies confirmation.

    3. **`projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/task-030-sme-walkthrough.md`**
       (NEW, ephemeral notes) â€” SME walkthrough record. Records: SME name + role
       + date of session + tenant (Spaarke Dev); paraphrased findings per
       question (NOT verbatim if customer-data-shaped); aggregate SME verdict
       per practice area (usable / partially usable / not usable + brief
       rationale); SME signoff statement (e.g., "Responses are usable for the
       intended Phase 1.5 acceptance bar"); ranked findings backlog (Sev-1
       blocks task 031; Sev-2/3 feeds R6 backlog).

    The 15-question matrix runs PASS (all 15 structurally conform to the
    binding contract; at least 12/15 are categorically usable per the rubric in
    Step 5) AND the SME walkthrough completes with signoff. Quality gates
    (`code-review` + `adr-check`) pass at Step 9.5.
  </goal>

