  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec SC-11 (binding success criterion)">`insights.query` tool registered in `SprkChatAgent`'s tool/skill registry; both response paths (playbook structured envelope + RAG citation-grounded prose) render correctly. Verify by: smoke test against Spaarke Dev with matter `da116923-d65a-f111-a825-3833c5d9bcb1`, project `27845394-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`, invoice `05c8ef8d-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4` (Wave D7 synthetic test entities).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec SC-18 (binding success criterion)">UX walkthrough with â‰¥1 legal-ops SME on Spaarke Dev â€” 5 realistic questions per practice area (CTRNS, IPPAT, BNKF) â€” responses usable. Verify by: SME signoff in walkthrough notes. SME signoff is REQUIRED for task completion â€” without signoff, the task is BLOCKED pending SME availability (escalate to operator).</constraint>
    <constraint source="integration brief Â§8 (binding acceptance criteria)">15-question matrix is 5 questions per practice area Ã— 3 practice areas (CTRNS contracts/transactional, IPPAT IP/patents, BNKF banking/finance). MUST run against Wave D7 synthetic GUIDs above. SME walkthrough is the binding completion criterion (1 SME minimum per integration brief Â§8 bullet 8).</constraint>
    <constraint source="integration brief Â§5.2 / ADR-018 (no information leakage)">Raw response content (LLM-generated answer text, citation excerpts, document content fragments) MUST NOT be committed into the test repo or task notes verbatim. Task notes record STRUCTURAL pass/fail + CATEGORICAL verdict (usable / partial / not usable) + paraphrased patterns. The synthetic test entities are designed to make this discipline easy (no real customer data), but the rule applies regardless â€” train the muscle memory.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md Â§3.5 / ADR-013 Â§3.5 Zone B boundary">R5 is a Zone B consumer of the Insights HTTP contract. Smoke tests assert WIRE-LEVEL behavior of the binding contract â€” they do NOT import or assert against any `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/` internals (handlers, classifiers, routing logic). The test references the contract envelope via R5-local types (mirror of task 029's `InsightsProblemDetails` + the success-shape types from task 026). NO `using Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Insights;` imports in the smoke test file.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md Â§3.1 / reuse mandate">MUST use the EXISTING `IntegrationTestFixture` pattern (see `tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/IntegrationTestFixture.cs`). DO NOT create a parallel test fixture, parallel auth bootstrap, or parallel HTTP client. The smoke tests MUST exercise the same R5 chat-agent tool handler (task 024 `InsightsQueryToolHandler`) that production traffic uses â€” testing the HTTP endpoint directly via `HttpClient` would miss the tool-catalog registration + middleware chain + correlation-id generation path that SC-11 requires verified.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md Â§3.6 / ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (this task adds test code + notes only; no `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` changes). Confirm in task notes; no `dotnet publish` measurement required.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md Â§10 / bff-extensions Â§F test obligation">This task IS the test obligation for the P2-G6/G7 Insights integration suite (tasks 024â€“029). The 15-question matrix is the integration test surface. Unit tests within tasks 024â€“029 cover internal behavior; this task covers end-to-end wire-level behavior.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-04 (anti-hallucination guarantee â€” RAG path)">RAG path returns `citations: []` AND `answer: ""` when retrieval finds zero hits. Smoke tests for empty-results scenarios MUST verify the empty-results branch renders correctly (per task 026's empty-results sub-renderer) â€” do NOT incorrectly mark these as failures. Empty results from synthetic entities on out-of-corpus questions is EXPECTED behavior, not a bug.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-11 (v1.1 graceful fallback)">If Wave F (Insights v1.1) has deployed to Spaarke Dev by smoke-test time, exercise SSE consumption + `citations[].href` clickable citations. If v1.1 has NOT deployed, exercise v1.0 fallback paths (single-shot response + display-name-only citations). EITHER state is acceptable per NFR-11 graceful fallback contract. Task notes MUST record which state was tested + the Wave F deployment status at test time.</constraint>
    <constraint source="integration brief Â§11 / ADR-016 (aggregate rate budget)">Aggregate budget is 60/min/oid across `/ask` + `/search` + `/assistant/query`. Smoke test executor (or SME) MUST NOT exceed this â€” pace the 15 questions across at least 1 minute (~4-second average inter-request gap). If 429 is observed during smoke testing, honor `Retry-After` (already verified by task 029 Test 9/10) â€” do NOT count as a smoke-test failure. Document the 429 occurrence in task notes as a positive validation that rate-limit handling works end-to-end.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (SME coordination)">SME availability is OPERATOR-DRIVEN. The AI agent prepares the walkthrough script + grading rubric + evidence-capture template but does NOT execute the SME session unsupervised. If no SME is available within the task's execution window, the AI agent completes the 15-question structural matrix + filed evidence + clearly marks the SME walkthrough as BLOCKED-ON-SME-AVAILABILITY; operator schedules SME and updates the task notes when complete. The task does NOT close until SME signoff is recorded (per spec SC-18 binding requirement).</constraint>
    <constraint source="integration brief Â§11 / Wave E deployment dependency">Smoke test execution requires `POST /api/insights/assistant/query` to be live on Spaarke Dev BFF â€” i.e., Insights r2 PR #337 (Wave E) MUST be merged to master + BFF redeployed. Verify by `GET https://spaarke-bff-dev.azurewebsites.net/swagger` â†’ `Insights` tag â†’ `InsightsAssistantQuery` endpoint present. If endpoint is NOT present, the task is BLOCKED pending Wave E ship (escalate; do NOT proceed with partial smoke tests).</constraint>
  </constraints>

