    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Existing integration test class scaffold" location="tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/PlaybookExecutionIntegrationTests.cs">
        Use the EXISTING `IntegrationTestFixture` + `[Collection("Integration")]`
        + `[Trait("Category", "Integration")]` pattern. Inject `IntegrationTestFixture`
        + `ITestOutputHelper` via constructor. Tests SKIP gracefully when fixture
        reports Spaarke Dev unreachable (existing pattern; do NOT change). Add a
        new `[Trait("Feature", "InsightsTool")]` discriminator so the smoke
        suite is independently runnable.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="15-question matrix shape (binding â€” integration brief Â§8 + spec SC-18)" location="(this task â€” defined in Step 5)">
        Three practice areas Ã— 5 questions each = 15 questions. Each entry has:
        (a) practice area (CTRNS / IPPAT / BNKF), (b) subject entity (one of
        the three Wave D7 GUIDs â€” diversified across the 15 entries), (c)
        natural-language query, (d) expected path (`playbook` / `rag` /
        `decline` / `empty-results`), (e) categorical pass rubric (what makes
        the response "usable" for this question). Author this matrix as a
        TypeScript-equivalent C# `theory` data source (xUnit `[Theory]` +
        `MemberData`) OR as a co-located JSON test-data file
        (`tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/fixtures/insights-smoke-matrix.json`)
        consumed by a single `[Theory]` test method. JSON-driven is preferred
        â€” it keeps the question text out of compiled artifacts and centralizes
        the matrix for easy update.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Question seed source (background â€” decision-tree guide)" location="docs/guides/INSIGHTS-PLAYBOOK-VS-RAG-DECISION-TREE.md">
        The decision-tree guide already contains 15 worked examples across
        CTRNS / IPPAT / BNKF (per integration brief Â§A.1) â€” use these as the
        starting point for the smoke matrix. The 15 worked examples in the
        guide are already calibrated for the playbook-vs-RAG decision boundary,
        which exercises the classifier path (when `forceMode` is null) and the
        forced path (when `forceMode` is `playbook` or `rag`). Cross-reference
        + reuse where applicable; adjust as needed for synthetic-GUID
        applicability.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Categorical pass rubric (binding per integration brief Â§8)" location="(this task â€” defined in Step 5)">
        For each question, "usable" means ALL of:
        - Response status = 200 (or 200 with `structuredResult.kind = "decline"` â€”
          decline is a legitimate playbook outcome per integration brief Â§4.5).
        - Response shape conforms to binding contract (`path` âˆˆ {playbook, rag};
          `citations` is array; `confidence` âˆˆ [0,1]; `correlationId` present;
          `playbookId` present when `path = playbook`).
        - For RAG path: `citations[].source` is a recognizable document name (NOT
          empty when `answer` is non-empty); `[n]` tokens in `answer` match
          `citations[].n` values (no orphans).
        - For playbook path: `structuredResult.envelope` is non-empty (or
          decline envelope is well-formed with `Reason` + `MinimumEvidenceNeeded` +
          `SuggestedActions`).
        - For empty-results: BOTH `answer = ""` AND `citations = []` (per FR-04
          anti-hallucination contract).
        - No raw stack traces, document content fragments, or prompt text in
          `answer` field (the BFF strips these per ADR-018; smoke test re-verifies).

        SME categorical verdict is qualitative â€” "would a legal-ops practitioner
        find this response useful in their workflow?". Capture per question +
        aggregate per practice area.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Correlation-id end-to-end propagation verification (spec FR-17 / SC-16)" location="(integration test assertion)">
        For at least one question per practice area (3 total minimum), capture
        the request's `x-correlation-id` header value (generated by task 024
        per Assistant turn). Assert that:
        (a) The response's `X-Insights-*` headers OR ProblemDetails
            `correlationId` extension echoes the same value.
        (b) If Spaarke Dev App Insights / Kusto is operator-accessible, the
            operator runs a sample trace lookup (e.g.,
            `requests | where customDimensions.correlationId == "&lt;captured-id&gt;"`)
            and captures the trace-count + result reference (NOT the trace
            body) in task notes.

        This verifies SC-16 end-to-end propagation pre-Phase-2-close.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="SME walkthrough script template" location="(this task â€” co-located in walkthrough notes)">
        Walkthrough session structure (operator-led, ~30â€“45 min):
        1. SME orientation (5 min): explain Spaarke Dev synthetic entities,
           Wave D7 GUIDs, the chat-agent tool surface, the goal (Phase 1.5
           usability acceptance).
        2. 15-question walkthrough (25â€“30 min): operator drives the chat-agent
           UI; SME observes responses; per question, SME assigns categorical
           verdict (usable / partial / not usable) + brief paraphrased note.
        3. Aggregate verdict per practice area (5 min): SME synthesizes
           overall practice-area assessment.
        4. Signoff (5 min): SME states "Responses are usable for Phase 1.5
           acceptance bar" OR identifies specific blockers + Sev rating.

        Operator captures notes during session; AI agent compiles + structures
        them into the evidence file after the session.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="No-raw-content evidence discipline (binding per integration brief Â§5.2 + ADR-018)" location="(task notes authoring)">
        When recording evidence in `task-030-smoke-evidence.md` /
        `task-030-sme-walkthrough.md`, follow these explicit rules:
        - Question text: OK to record verbatim (synthetic questions about
          synthetic entities; no customer data risk).
        - Response answer text: paraphrase or abstract (e.g., "Answer cited
          Closing Memo + Acme APA across 3 citations; confidence 0.81;
          structurally well-formed") â€” do NOT paste the full answer.
        - Citation source names: OK to record (synthetic document names).
        - Citation excerpt fields: paraphrase ONLY â€” do NOT paste verbatim
          even though synthetic (rule discipline).
        - LLM-generated content beyond the answer/citations: ignore entirely.
        - CorrelationId values: OK to record verbatim (opaque debugging keys).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Wave F deployment status pre-flight check" location="(this task â€” Step 2)">
        Before authoring the smoke matrix, the agent MUST verify:
        - Spaarke Dev BFF endpoint live: `GET /swagger` shows
          `InsightsAssistantQuery` in `Insights` tag.
        - Wave F (v1.1) deployment status: check
          `notes/insights-r2-coordination.md` Â§8 changelog for the most recent
          Wave F update. If Wave F has shipped (SSE + `citations[].href`
          available), the smoke matrix targets v1.1 behavior. If Wave F has
          NOT shipped, the matrix targets v1.0 single-shot + display-name-only
          citations + the v1.1 fallback paths from tasks 026/027.
        - Either state is contract-acceptable per NFR-11; the choice affects
          test design, not pass/fail.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
